⚙️ Implementation Steps
Step 1: Install the Remi Repository

The default Enterprise Linux repositories did not provide PHP-FPM 8.3. To install the required version, I first enabled the Remi repository.

dnf install https://rpms.remirepo.net/enterprise/remi-release-9.rpm -y
Step 2: Install Nginx
dnf install nginx -y

Verify installation:

nginx -v
Step 3: Install PHP-FPM 8.3
dnf install php-fpm -y

Verify the installed version:

php-fpm -v
Step 4: Configure PHP-FPM

Created the socket directory:

mkdir -p /var/run/php-fpm

Edited:

/etc/php-fpm.d/www.conf

Updated the following settings:

user = nginx
group = nginx

listen = /var/run/php-fpm/default.sock

listen.owner = nginx
listen.group = nginx
listen.mode = 0660
Step 5: Configure Nginx

Edited the default virtual host configuration and configured:

Listen on port 8091
Document root as /var/www/html
PHP processing through the Unix socket
server {

    listen 8091;

    server_name _;

    root /var/www/html;

    index index.php index.html;

    location ~ \.php$ {

        fastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php-fpm/default.sock;

        fastcgi_index index.php;

        include fastcgi_params;

        fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $document_root$fastcgi_script_name;

    }

}
Step 6: Validate Configuration

Validate PHP-FPM configuration:

php-fpm -t

Validate Nginx configuration:

nginx -t
Step 7: Enable and Start Services
systemctl enable nginx --now
systemctl enable php-fpm --now

systemctl restart nginx
systemctl restart php-fpm
Step 8: Verify the Unix Socket
ls -l /var/run/php-fpm/

Expected output:

default.sock
Step 9: Test the Application

From the jump host:

curl http://stapp02:8091/index.php

The command successfully returned the PHP application, confirming that Nginx and PHP-FPM were communicating correctly through the Unix socket.

