🌍 Production Relevance

This deployment architecture is widely used in production environments because it offers improved performance and security.

Common use cases include:

WordPress hosting
Laravel applications
CodeIgniter deployments
Magento and other e-commerce platforms
Internal enterprise PHP applications

Using Unix sockets instead of TCP reduces communication overhead while limiting PHP-FPM access to local processes only.

